The lightweight, three-panel designed respirator helps provide comfortable and convenient respiratory protection. 3M uses a variety of innovative technologies and features to help you meet your respiratory protection and comfort needs. 3M`s proprietary filter media, 3M Advanced Electret Media, filters dust and other airborne particles, while allowing for easy breathing. The soft inner material provides added comfort and the adjustable nose clip help provide a custom seal.

manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Fitting Instructions. Must be followed each time respirator is worn. Remove respirator from packaging and hold with straps facing upward. Place bottom strap under center flaps next to WARNING statement. Fully open both panels. Bend nosepiece around thumb at center of foam to separate straps.

Steps follows Foam should rest on nose with bottom panel open. Position top strap high on the back of the head. Position bottom strap around neck, below ears. Adjust for comfort. Using both hands, fix the entire nose area to the shape of nose by pushing inward. Check seal per user instructions. If you CANNOT achieve a proper fit, DO NOT enter the contaminated area.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 15, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Easy to breathe in! Runs small.
reviews.reviewText: These are amazing for longer term wear. They’re comfortable though do run narrow and leave an imprint across your cheeks after taking them off.I love that they’re easy to breathe in and don’t suction to your face when inhaling.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 12, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Comfortable and hardly any fogging of my glasses
reviews.reviewText: These are very comfortable and secure fitting, and don't put unpleasant pressure on the bridge of my nose like my previous rigid 3M (#8511) N95 mask did. The foam nose band runs all across the inside top and provides a comfortable, moldable, snug seal that does a better job of keeping my glasses from fogging than my previous mask, except if I exhale with a big sigh through my mouth or nose, but even then, the fogging is slight and dissipates quickly. I wasn’t able to wear my glasses in the correct position with my rigid mask, but don’t have that problem with this mask.Breathing in this one is a little warmer than my previous KN95 and valved #8511, and on warm days I can feel the beginnings of a little bit of sweat above and below my lip , but it's worth it for me to have the full, all-around close fit protection an N95 mask provides that KN95's don't. I like that they fold flat for carrying around.In case this is helpful, I have an average sized head and full face with a square-ish jaw. The mask sits higher on the bridge of my nose than on the guy in the picture--about half inch above the inside corner of my eyes, is 8" (accounting for the “duck bill” expansion) from the top to the bottom of the chin tab and about 6” side to side on the widest part of the chin tab area.A reviewer said the mask smelled like pickle or salt and vinegar chips and I agree, they do smell a bit like that (it’s the foam nose band and not the mask itself), but it didn’t bother me and like the same reviewer said, you don’t notice it after a while. It did NOT smell like burnt rubber mentioned in another review.The middle part is stiff like the rigid N95s, but the top and bottom part are a soft, flexible (kind of reminds me of slightly worn jeans) and what appears to be more breathable fabric. The straps look like long wide, flat rubber bands and appear to be securely stapled--I pulled pretty hard on them at the ends and they didn’t move from under the staples. Since they’re smooth, they slide down my hair if I don’t put them high enough on my head, but they’ re comfortable in that position and I hardly notice them at all.I was looking for something to replace my rigid, valved N95s and I'm happy with these.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 12, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Easy to Breathe
reviews.reviewText: Some masks make it hard to breathe and they smell awful but this one doesn't. I primarily use them when I'm flying so that I have that added layer of protection as most have ditched masks but they haven't ditched being nasty with their uncovered coughs and sneezes. I don't use the blue straps so I can't speak to the level of comfort with something over your head, but I punch small holes on the ends and thread a hair tie through to make ear loops. I find this comfortable and easy to take off and put back on when at TSA checkpoints or if I need to eat or drink. The nose is flexible and has padding to add to the comfort. I do thing they're pricy, but when protecting your health if you can afford them, get them.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 17, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Supposedly an N95 mask is more protective against Omicron
reviews.reviewText: It seems like a decent mask. I’m 5’7” with a regular-sized face and chin. This masks fits, but just barely, my little face. If I had a slightly longer chin, the bottom of the mask would ride up. There is no stretch whatsoever to this mask; the straps have stretch, but not the mask. I’m not a fan of the behind-the-head straps, but I understand that type of strap is required to get the NIOSH approval and because it supposedly provides a better seal. On my face, the mask does create a tight, cup-like seal. It has a really good, padded nose wire. I find it fairly easy to breathe through. It also doesn’t smash my nose as much as all my cloth masks do.Mine has a gross odor which doesn’t seem like it’s healthy to be inhaling all day. The mask starts to hurt my face and head after about 10 minutes. On me, the mask is a tight fit. I guess that gives it a good seal, but that also creates uncomfortable pressure on the face and head. When I take the mask off, the imprint of the mask remains on my face and there’s a lot of moisture on my face. I’d never get through more than an hour of wearing this mask because I just want to tear it off my face.So, basically, I prefer my cloth masks because they are comfortable, have stretch, have ear straps, and are black in color, but according to all that I’ve read so far they are not very protective against Omicron. This 3M mask provides better Omicron protection but I find it way less comfortable and I don’t like the smell.
